    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Offered here is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 naturally aspirated 3.2L inline-six. This high-revving power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and double VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is routed through a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission to the rear wheels via an M Variable Differential Lock, ensuring optimal traction and corner-exit stability. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a reinforced rear subframe and updated bushings to maintain lateral rigidity. Suspension geometry is dialed for spirited driving, featuring MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup. This example exhibits the visceral analog feedback enthusiasts crave, with recent cooling system overhaul and rod bearing service performed for long-term reliability. A true driver\u2019s specimen that balances mechanical purity with daily usability.",
